        "id": 2302912,
        "name": "David Bueker",
        "username": "David_Bu3ker",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_bu3ker/{size}/319725_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-24T00:39:05.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=36616&amp;iNote=6700819\"><strong>2002 Domaine Georges Mugneret/Mugneret-Gibourg Ruchottes-Chambertin</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Ruchottes-Chambertin Grand Cru (11/23/2017)</em><br>\nAir, air, air, we gave this lots of air. It rewarded us with floral, Earth, spice, red fruit and cedar tones and a sensual palate presence. It did have a bit of back end grip, but that just added weight and presence, conveying its Grand Cru status. Four hours after opening I am sitting with the last few drops, and it is kaleidoscopic and haunting. This is what great Burgundy should be. It takes the expectations, sets them up, and knocks them down.</p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
